<h2 id="org12a04ab"><span class="section-number-2">4.</span> <span class="todo TODO">TODO</span> No discussion, self-reflection or even communication between different branches is allowed?</h2>
<div class="outline-text-2" id="text-4">
<p>
I don't get why the members who left Acorn in my branch left so quietly, same applies for Acorn Oxford. I feel like I'm taking crazy pills talking to members in Acorn today who want to keep all the issues we're facing as an organisation secret. How will most members even know there is a problem if we don't ever acknowledge it?
</p>

<p>
Bafflingly one of the demands of the Oxford is to talk
</p>

<p>
I feel like I understand just tip of the iceberg when it comes to understanding what's going on and why. As I find out more, I will add to this site.
</p>

<p>
Some of the discussions that have resulted in member repression is around Refugee and declaring solidarity with Palestine.
</p>

<p>
Issue is not <i>necessarily</i> with some of the strategic decisions that National have taken - I understand the arguments as to why taking explicitly communist policies (having official positions in-solidarity with immigrants, Palestine solidarity) - it is more that the . It is like there is a suspicion of the membership itself, like every single conversation is happening in
</p>

<p>
The branch
